This bug occurs on I20031203 as well. It seems to be somehow related to a 3rd
party plugin/feature.

If I start with no plugins the image starts. 

If I then proceed to add the  plugins a couple at a time then at some point I
get an error when starting the image could not restore Workbench layout (stack
trace below) followed with the error reported in my first post.

I was also able to add all the plugins back and still start the image but adding
the features back caused the error again.

I then added just the  features first along with their associated plugins and
retried and it did start fine. 

So it seems to be a problem with a combination of the features and plugins plus
underlying platform. I could not identify a single feature or plugin that was
the cause of the problem.

At this point the workspace is corrupt. Even if I remove the plugins/features I
can no longer use the workspace. I get the error reported in my first post.

If I delete the .config and workspace directories I can once again start the image.
